      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must have documented version control, regression test suite, and release notes covering the hemolysis scalar transport module.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023 R1 is used under a documented QA plan including version-locked release, regression test suite results, and configuration management records. All SQA requirements for MRL 2 are satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must pass at least one published benchmark problem relevant to rotating turbomachinery or scalar transport.",
      "rationale": "Code verification is demonstrated via the ASME V&V 20 lid-driven cavity benchmark and the rotating channel flow benchmark published in the ANSYS verification manual. Both confirm second-order spatial accuracy consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for shear-stress-derived hemolysis index must be below 5% on the fine grid.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation study conducted at the 6 LPM / 3000 RPM design point. GCI on the fine mesh (12.4 M cells) is 3.1% for the volume-averaged hemolysis index, satisfying the 5% threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be replicated within ±5% in the simulation setup.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds from the FDA bench study are reproduced within 2% in the CFD boundary conditions. Blood analog viscosity (36% glycerol-water) is matched to within 1.5% at 37 °C. Test condition fidelity is adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental NIH within 15% across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values range from 0.0031 to 0.0089 g/100 L across the five operating points. Comparison with FDA experimental data shows a maximum deviation of 11.4%, meeting the 15% acceptance criterion at all points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution, relative hemolysis ratio RH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint and the acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate. This scalar directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion and is computed from the same shear-stress power-law model used in published FDA guidance. Relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid analog, and flow regime as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation is performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry using the same 36% glycerol-water blood analog at physiologically representative flow rates (2–8 LPM) and speeds (2500–4500 RPM). The validation domain overlaps the COU operating envelope, supporting adequacy at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor beyond code verification evidence already captured.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, explicit iterative solver error quantification beyond residual convergence monitoring is not required. Residuals for continuity, momentum, and scalar transport converge to below 1×10⁻⁵. Factor scoped to Gradation 1 and satisfied by default."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst training records and simulation plan provide sufficient assurance.",
      "rationale": "Simulation plan reviewed by a senior analyst. Analyst holds documented CFD training credentials. Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2 for Class II device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 beyond selection rationale for turbulence and hemolysis sub-models.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump applications. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be traceable to calibrated measurements or published reference data with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry is derived from CMM-verified CAD files (±0.02 mm tolerance). Fluid properties are sourced from the boundary-condition dataset (https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-boundary-condition-dataset), which was compiled from calibrated viscometer and densitometer measurements. The dataset dataVintage predates the most recent model revision by approximately three weeks; the revision addressed impeller blade trailing-edge chamfer refinement only, and the fluid property inputs are geometry-independent. The team judged the dataset remained applicable without re-measurement, though no formal re-validation was performed to confirm this position."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; FDA pump is a standard reference geometry with published dimensional specifications.",
      "rationale": "The FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is a publicly documented reference geometry. Sample-to-sample dimensional variability is not assessed at MRL 2 for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in validation simulations must match those used in the COU simulations within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table confirms that fluid viscosity, density, inlet flow waveform, and rotational speed inputs are identical between validation and COU simulation sets. Differences in geometric fidelity (chamfer refinement introduced in model revision v3r2) are documented and assessed as non-material to hemolysis QoI, consistent with the rationale applied to the boundary-condition dataset."
    }
